Introduction  This is a compilation about my understanding of the 2008 GFC.
  Causes of the crisis    Shadow banking expanding market-based credit with riskier assets (hedged with derivatives to become quasi-treasuries)
  price of this assets declined, dealers could not access the usual funding liquidity to roll their loans;
  with no access to cash from market-based credit, they were forced to sell their securities;
